1
00:00:07,332 --> 00:00:10,399
I'm glad we beat that forest dragon
without any losses.

2
00:00:10,402 --> 00:00:10,502
I'm glad we beat that forest dragon
without any losses.

3
00:00:10,878 --> 00:00:13,211
Those ramparts you made
served their purpose.

4
00:00:13,838 --> 00:00:16,880
That's true. Without them,
it might've been a different story.

5
00:00:16,967 --> 00:00:19,134
I have a proposal, Lord Van.

6
00:00:19,219 --> 00:00:21,428
Now that you've made
those sturdy ramparts,

7
00:00:21,513 --> 00:00:24,471
why not turn your attention
to city planning next?

8
00:00:24,808 --> 00:00:26,391
City planning?

9
00:00:26,476 --> 00:00:30,726
You mentioned before that I should aim
to build a city for 10,000 to live in.

10
00:00:30,814 --> 00:00:31,855
Yes.

11
00:00:31,940 --> 00:00:37,398
To accomplish that and fashion an
attractive city, we'll need new residents.

12
00:00:37,696 --> 00:00:39,154
I see.

13
00:00:39,239 --> 00:00:40,406
Lord Van.

14
00:00:41,241 --> 00:00:45,491
Bell and Rango have returned with folk
from the Mary Chamber of Commerce.

15
00:00:45,579 --> 00:00:49,245
They said they'd buy the materials
from the forest dragon.

16
00:00:49,583 --> 00:00:50,666
Great.

17
00:00:51,125 --> 00:00:53,542
First, we'll sell the dragon materials.

18
00:00:53,628 --> 00:00:56,337
Then we'll make a city
everyone can enjoy living in.

19
00:01:08,392 --> 00:01:13,476
EASYGOING TERRITORY DEFENSE
BY THE OPTIMISTIC LORD

20
00:01:13,564 --> 00:01:16,147
EPISODE 7: EARNEST MERCHANTS
AND RECEIVING A PROUD TITLE

21
00:02:26,970 --> 00:02:28,595
EPISODE 7: EARNEST MERCHANTS
AND RECEIVING A PROUD TITLE

22
00:02:28,680 --> 00:02:32,513
I wonder how much the Mary Chamber
of Commerce merchants will buy them for.

23
00:02:32,893 --> 00:02:34,226
It's a dragon.

24
00:02:34,311 --> 00:02:36,477
A large forest dragon at that.

25
00:02:36,563 --> 00:02:41,021
Its scales, claws, fangs, and eyes
are all in pretty good condition.

26
00:02:41,318 --> 00:02:44,776
You'll probably get at least 100 platinum.

27
00:02:45,238 --> 00:02:49,655
If I remember correctly, one platinum
is worth around 100 million yen.

28
00:02:49,742 --> 00:02:51,409
So 100 would mean...

29
00:02:52,245 --> 00:02:54,579
A dragon is worth 10 billion yen?!

30
00:02:54,664 --> 00:02:56,747
Did I just win the jackpot?

31
00:02:57,209 --> 00:02:59,292
I had my doubts, but...

32
00:02:59,377 --> 00:03:00,919
It's real, all right.

33
00:03:01,754 --> 00:03:03,088
So what do you think?

34
00:03:03,172 --> 00:03:08,047
Lord Van. Please entrust these materials
to the Mary Chamber of Commerce.

35
00:03:08,135 --> 00:03:11,594
We're the most reputable traders
and have the royal family's backing,

36
00:03:11,681 --> 00:03:14,973
so we'll buy them from you
at the highest price you'll get, too.

37
00:03:15,059 --> 00:03:16,934
That's great news.

38
00:03:17,019 --> 00:03:19,269
By the way, how much can we sell them for?

39
00:03:19,355 --> 00:03:24,438
Given the current market,
I'd say about 60 platinum.

40
00:03:24,944 --> 00:03:28,194
Huh? I thought I'd won the jackpot.

41
00:03:28,906 --> 00:03:31,573
Wait there a sec.
I'll consult with Bell and Rango.

42
00:03:31,659 --> 00:03:33,159
Oh, please hold on a minute.

43
00:03:33,285 --> 00:03:37,619
Those brothers are still young
as merchants go. We can offer a proper—

44
00:03:37,707 --> 00:03:40,832
Sounds like we might not get
as much as I thought.

45
00:03:40,918 --> 00:03:42,835
They quoted me 60 platinum.

46
00:03:42,920 --> 00:03:44,420
That's crazy.

47
00:03:44,505 --> 00:03:46,963
It's obvious this is
all of the highest quality.

48
00:03:47,299 --> 00:03:48,424
You imbeciles!

49
00:03:48,509 --> 00:03:53,050
You two are part of the Mary Chamber
of Commerce, too, y'know. Play along!

50
00:03:53,139 --> 00:03:54,972
H-Hold on a second.

51
00:03:55,099 --> 00:03:58,641
As merchants, we should give
a proper appraisal.

52
00:03:58,727 --> 00:04:03,852
No other merchants are coming
to this remote village for a whole year!

53
00:04:04,233 --> 00:04:07,733
Even if we only offer 60 platinum,
that brat has no choice but to sell.

54
00:04:07,819 --> 00:04:10,861
Got it? Now shut up and do as we say!

55
00:04:11,365 --> 00:04:14,407
I can hear you all as well.

56
00:04:14,493 --> 00:04:19,576
Well, one platinum is worth 100 million.
I guess I can't blame them for haggling.

57
00:04:19,665 --> 00:04:21,248
Even so...

58
00:04:21,542 --> 00:04:24,167
We brothers aim to do things fairly,

59
00:04:24,252 --> 00:04:28,127
no matter who we're dealing with
or what we're negotiating over.

60
00:04:28,214 --> 00:04:32,214
We believe that will lead
to greater future profit.

61
00:04:32,302 --> 00:04:34,468
And with Lord Van,
it'll definitely pay off!

62
00:04:34,555 --> 00:04:36,180
You dolts...

63
00:04:36,264 --> 00:04:40,806
When the president learns of this, you'll
be kicked out of Mary Chamber of Commerce.

64
00:04:44,981 --> 00:04:46,398
Imbeciles.

65
00:04:46,482 --> 00:04:48,274
They'll regret this!

66
00:04:49,444 --> 00:04:52,902
Are you sure? You'll be kicked out
of the Mary Chamber of Commerce.

67
00:04:52,989 --> 00:04:54,114
Yes.

68
00:04:54,199 --> 00:04:55,782
It was the only choice.

69
00:04:56,451 --> 00:04:57,742
Then, hey...

70
00:04:59,745 --> 00:05:01,954
Why not found your own trading company?

71
00:05:02,290 --> 00:05:03,748
Huh?!

72
00:05:04,167 --> 00:05:05,792
You make it sound easy.

73
00:05:05,877 --> 00:05:07,502
I-Is it difficult?

74
00:05:07,837 --> 00:05:11,420
You have to fulfill three conditions
to establish a trading company.

75
00:05:11,507 --> 00:05:13,674
First, pay the Merchants' Guild
registration fee.

76
00:05:13,759 --> 00:05:15,384
Second, own your own shop.

77
00:05:15,470 --> 00:05:18,553
And third, get an endorsement
from a titled noble.

78
00:05:18,931 --> 00:05:23,181
The first two are easy enough,
but that last one's an issue.

79
00:05:23,894 --> 00:05:28,019
The only person with a title
who's likely to help us is...

80
00:05:28,941 --> 00:05:30,149
Sure, I don't mind.

81
00:05:30,401 --> 00:05:32,151
Huh? You'll do it?

82
00:05:32,445 --> 00:05:35,445
I hear the Mary Chamber of Commerce
is favored by the royal family.

83
00:05:35,531 --> 00:05:37,573
Won't they harass you?

84
00:05:37,658 --> 00:05:39,367
Think about it.

85
00:05:39,952 --> 00:05:43,410
If I found a small trading company
as a newly elevated noble,

86
00:05:43,498 --> 00:05:45,748
recognizing it is no skin off their noses.

87
00:05:45,833 --> 00:05:49,041
If anything, it'd be a bad look
for the royal family if they didn't.

88
00:05:49,294 --> 00:05:50,711
I see.

89
00:05:50,796 --> 00:05:53,463
Besides, I have no land
or knights of my own,

90
00:05:53,549 --> 00:05:55,424
so if I want to climb the ladder,

91
00:05:55,509 --> 00:05:58,675
I need to do things
that will get people talking.

92
00:05:58,763 --> 00:06:03,429
If I do this, word will spread that
I helped two earnest merchants.

93
00:06:03,517 --> 00:06:08,308
In that case, why not say
you defeated that dragon, Panamera?

94
00:06:08,647 --> 00:06:12,563
People will talk about that,
and it means my family won't find out.

95
00:06:12,651 --> 00:06:15,192
Your thought process
has the oddest blind spots.

96
00:06:15,570 --> 00:06:17,612
Dragons are rarely slain.

97
00:06:17,697 --> 00:06:21,656
Even if I said I'd killed it, they'd want
to know in detail how I'd managed it,

98
00:06:21,743 --> 00:06:25,035
and their own investigations
would lead to you anyway.

99
00:06:28,167 --> 00:06:31,167
What will I do if my family
summons me home?

100
00:06:31,253 --> 00:06:32,878
There's one way to avoid that.

101
00:06:32,962 --> 00:06:34,171
Huh?

102
00:06:34,256 --> 00:06:36,464
It's simple. Get yourself a title.

103
00:06:36,883 --> 00:06:38,175
A title?

104
00:06:38,593 --> 00:06:41,385
All nobles have a title.

105
00:06:41,471 --> 00:06:44,721
I've worked my way up
from knight, the lowest title,

106
00:06:44,808 --> 00:06:47,349
but since you're the son of a marquis,

107
00:06:47,436 --> 00:06:50,061
they'd probably make you
a baron to start with.

108
00:06:50,605 --> 00:06:54,397
Lord Van, get yourself a title
and found a new house.

109
00:06:54,484 --> 00:06:56,609
What is this woman saying?

110
00:06:57,111 --> 00:07:00,195
You just need to declare
that you slew the dragon.

111
00:07:00,281 --> 00:07:03,364
All I really did was pin it down.

112
00:07:04,118 --> 00:07:08,077
No way. That would make me
really stand out, wouldn't it?

113
00:07:08,164 --> 00:07:09,664
And that dissatisfies you?

114
00:07:09,958 --> 00:07:13,416
You can become famous for being
the eight-year-old who slew a dragon,

115
00:07:13,502 --> 00:07:15,961
and use that achievement
to earn a title.

116
00:07:17,631 --> 00:07:18,715
That said...

117
00:07:19,633 --> 00:07:21,842
I do understand how you feel, young man.

118
00:07:21,928 --> 00:07:25,136
When I first earned my title,
I gained more enemies,

119
00:07:25,223 --> 00:07:27,973
and people trying to use me
came out of the woodwork.

120
00:07:28,101 --> 00:07:29,226
However...

121
00:07:30,436 --> 00:07:32,936
I reduced all of them to ash.

122
00:07:33,147 --> 00:07:34,606
To ash?

123
00:07:34,690 --> 00:07:38,773
So if any new enemies show up, don't
hesitate to fire your ballistae at them.

124
00:07:38,861 --> 00:07:42,236
A dozen corpses in your wake
will stop people opposing you.

125
00:07:43,699 --> 00:07:46,574
I just learned a terrifying tip
for navigating life.

126
00:07:47,035 --> 00:07:49,494
But if I claim it was all my doing,

127
00:07:49,580 --> 00:07:52,455
you can't use it to support
your own bid for promotion.

128
00:07:52,541 --> 00:07:53,666
Young man.

129
00:07:54,377 --> 00:07:57,127
Are you worried about me?

130
00:07:57,630 --> 00:08:01,963
I don't think I've done anything to have
an-eight-year old worrying about me,

131
00:08:02,050 --> 00:08:03,550
so perhaps I misheard.

132
00:08:03,636 --> 00:08:05,469
No, I didn't mean it.

133
00:08:05,554 --> 00:08:08,221
In fact, I'm now worried
about my own safety.

134
00:08:08,306 --> 00:08:09,931
Please don't eat me.

135
00:08:11,602 --> 00:08:14,769
You always have an amusing retort.

136
00:08:15,313 --> 00:08:18,480
Don't worry. I won't eat you
for another five years.

137
00:08:18,567 --> 00:08:20,776
So to help you grow even bigger,

138
00:08:20,861 --> 00:08:23,986
I'll let you take the glory
for slaying this dragon.

139
00:08:25,949 --> 00:08:27,491
I don't believe it.

140
00:08:27,575 --> 00:08:30,284
I apparently only have
five years left to live.

141
00:08:31,454 --> 00:08:33,579
Huh?! Lady Panamera?!

142
00:08:33,665 --> 00:08:36,581
She'll endorse us?!

143
00:08:36,668 --> 00:08:37,959
That means...

144
00:08:38,045 --> 00:08:41,336
Yup. You can found your own
trading company, Bell and Rango.

145
00:08:41,423 --> 00:08:43,423
All right!

146
00:08:46,428 --> 00:08:50,261
Getting down to it, will you please
sell those dragon materials to us?

147
00:08:50,348 --> 00:08:51,932
Of course.

148
00:08:52,017 --> 00:08:56,809
We want to repay you for all you've done
for us, so how does 130 platinum sound?

149
00:08:56,896 --> 00:08:58,188
That much?

150
00:08:58,606 --> 00:09:01,315
Thanks. We have a deal.

151
00:09:01,609 --> 00:09:02,693
Right!

152
00:09:03,278 --> 00:09:06,320
Okay, let's go to the royal capital
to sell all this stuff.

153
00:09:07,449 --> 00:09:09,574
There aren't any carriages?

154
00:09:09,659 --> 00:09:15,034
Right. The Mary Chamber of Commerce
merchants just left with it.

155
00:09:15,122 --> 00:09:16,914
What were they thinking?

156
00:09:17,750 --> 00:09:20,709
They're waiting for you
to come crying to them.

157
00:09:21,045 --> 00:09:25,378
If you can't transport the goods,
you have no choice but to listen to them.

158
00:09:27,176 --> 00:09:30,134
Then, I'll make a new
carriage for you two.

159
00:09:30,221 --> 00:09:31,387
You will?

160
00:09:31,472 --> 00:09:35,972
In that case, you can have
my warhorse to pull the carriage.

161
00:09:36,102 --> 00:09:40,560
They're well-trained, and their stamina
and speed are on another level.

162
00:09:44,861 --> 00:09:48,194
I bet Bell and Rango are
regretting their decision now.

163
00:09:48,239 --> 00:09:49,655
Those foolish brothers.

164
00:09:49,740 --> 00:09:52,406
They'll come crying to us in no time.

165
00:09:54,411 --> 00:09:56,245
Wh-What's that?

166
00:09:56,622 --> 00:09:58,497
Viscountess Cayenne?

167
00:10:03,254 --> 00:10:06,045
That was Bell and Rango, wasn't it?

168
00:10:06,132 --> 00:10:07,757
Why were they with the viscountess?

169
00:10:08,967 --> 00:10:10,009
H-Hold on a sec...

170
00:10:10,427 --> 00:10:14,427
With the cooperation of a noble, they
could start their own trading company!

171
00:10:15,599 --> 00:10:19,016
No way!

172
00:10:21,062 --> 00:10:24,312
KINGDOM OF SCUDERIA
ROYAL CAPITAL, AUDIENCE CHAMBER

173
00:10:25,108 --> 00:10:27,025
So the social climber is here again.

174
00:10:27,444 --> 00:10:32,444
Still, I assumed you had come
to petition me for a higher rank.

175
00:10:32,533 --> 00:10:35,699
Yet you want me to grant
a title to someone else?

176
00:10:36,244 --> 00:10:37,494
That's correct...

177
00:10:37,954 --> 00:10:39,038
King Dino.

178
00:10:39,122 --> 00:10:42,039
KINGDOM OF SCUDERIA'S KING
DINO EN TSORA BELLRINET

179
00:10:42,292 --> 00:10:47,083
Viscountess Cayenne, I do not see
this man you seek a title for.

180
00:10:47,172 --> 00:10:49,672
The man in question is the lord
of a remote village.

181
00:10:49,758 --> 00:10:54,175
He's currently shoring up his village, so
he couldn't make it to the royal capital.

182
00:10:54,429 --> 00:10:57,179
Why would you recommend
such a man to the nobility?

183
00:10:57,557 --> 00:11:01,932
For his great deeds so far, and
his potential that overshadows them.

184
00:11:02,645 --> 00:11:03,895
Oh?

185
00:11:03,980 --> 00:11:08,272
Given your prowess, for you to recommend
him means I can expect great things, yes?

186
00:11:08,359 --> 00:11:12,818
Still, what manner of feats could
he have achieved in a village so remote,

187
00:11:12,863 --> 00:11:15,280
we haven't stationed troops
or knights there?

188
00:11:15,866 --> 00:11:18,533
He slew a forest dragon.

189
00:11:18,869 --> 00:11:20,661
What? Is that even possible?

190
00:11:20,746 --> 00:11:23,246
And he "slew" it? He didn't drive it off?

191
00:11:23,333 --> 00:11:26,416
Is this lord an elemental mage?

192
00:11:26,502 --> 00:11:29,544
No, his magical aptitude
is for production magic.

193
00:11:29,630 --> 00:11:31,547
Production magic?

194
00:11:31,632 --> 00:11:33,132
Who is this man?

195
00:11:33,218 --> 00:11:35,218
The son of Marquis Fertio,

196
00:11:35,303 --> 00:11:36,636
Van Nei Fertio.

197
00:11:36,721 --> 00:11:38,721
A lord who is barely eight years old.

198
00:11:39,181 --> 00:11:42,931
Oh? An eight year old child
in charge of a remote village?

199
00:11:43,018 --> 00:11:44,477
Give me more details.

200
00:11:44,562 --> 00:11:49,062
I will. The moment that young boy arrived
in the village he was to rule over,

201
00:11:49,149 --> 00:11:51,608
he found it under attack by bandits.

202
00:11:52,152 --> 00:11:55,402
However, he protected the village
and killed the bandits

203
00:11:55,489 --> 00:11:58,572
with the few subordinates
and adventurers escorting him.

204
00:11:59,368 --> 00:12:02,618
Aha. So he joined battle
and triumphed at such a young age?

205
00:12:02,913 --> 00:12:05,872
After that, the young boy
used his production magic

206
00:12:05,958 --> 00:12:08,541
to surround the village
with walls, put in a moat,

207
00:12:08,627 --> 00:12:12,877
rebuild the ramshackle homes,
and improve the village's defenses.

208
00:12:13,382 --> 00:12:16,132
Then, this dragon attacked that village?

209
00:12:16,510 --> 00:12:21,843
Yes. I assisted in the slaying of the
dragon, but all I did was pin it down.

210
00:12:21,932 --> 00:12:24,724
Lord Van and his subordinates
used their strength

211
00:12:24,809 --> 00:12:27,684
to slay it without suffering
a single casualty.

212
00:12:28,272 --> 00:12:30,647
That sounds hard to believe.

213
00:12:34,069 --> 00:12:36,611
This is a fang from the slain dragon.

214
00:12:40,200 --> 00:12:42,409
I'd love for you to
come see, Your Majesty.

215
00:12:42,702 --> 00:12:47,619
To see how much this village has changed
in its short time under Van's stewardship.

216
00:12:49,125 --> 00:12:52,708
I'm sure a man as wise as Your Majesty
would make him the lord

217
00:12:52,796 --> 00:12:56,671
of a territory even greater in size
for the sake of our nation's defense.

218
00:12:57,676 --> 00:12:59,176
Interesting.

219
00:12:59,803 --> 00:13:03,844
Van Nei Fertio, huh? I would like
to meet him as soon as possible.

220
00:13:05,266 --> 00:13:08,391
Let it be known that
Van Nei Fertio slew a dragon!

221
00:13:08,477 --> 00:13:09,977
To honor this achievement,

222
00:13:10,104 --> 00:13:12,604
he has been made a baron!

223
00:13:12,857 --> 00:13:15,191
That's Marquis Fertio's son.

224
00:13:15,276 --> 00:13:17,359
The fourth son they called a prodigy?

225
00:13:17,445 --> 00:13:19,320
A child slew a dragon?

226
00:13:19,948 --> 00:13:23,531
Well, young man,
things are about to get interesting.

227
00:13:24,911 --> 00:13:26,494
You'd better be grateful.

228
00:13:30,249 --> 00:13:32,666
After Panamera and
the others left the village,

229
00:13:32,751 --> 00:13:35,543
I remade the uniform houses
into something fancier,

230
00:13:35,629 --> 00:13:37,963
then reconstructed the village center.

231
00:13:38,382 --> 00:13:41,007
All in all, my city building
was proceeding smoothly.

232
00:13:41,302 --> 00:13:42,594
Then, in addition to that...

233
00:13:44,305 --> 00:13:45,555
I built some towers.

234
00:13:47,516 --> 00:13:49,808
They're incredibly tall.

235
00:13:49,893 --> 00:13:51,643
And you've made two of them.

236
00:13:51,729 --> 00:13:52,895
Yup.

237
00:13:53,189 --> 00:13:57,564
This one's Oligo Tower, and the one
on the other side is Grape Tower.

238
00:13:58,151 --> 00:14:02,693
Towers serve as symbols of a settlement
and allow us to detect enemies from afar,

239
00:14:02,781 --> 00:14:04,865
so this has also fortified our defenses.

240
00:14:05,618 --> 00:14:09,076
Everyone in the village can
now enjoy their lives in peace.

241
00:14:11,624 --> 00:14:14,832
Lord Van, I'll prepare
your lunch immediately.

242
00:14:14,918 --> 00:14:18,377
Oh, hey. Why don't we go eat lunch
at the top of the tower?

243
00:14:20,966 --> 00:14:22,174
Let's dig in.

244
00:14:23,761 --> 00:14:27,344
Till, your homemade egg
sandwiches are delicious.

245
00:14:27,430 --> 00:14:29,889
I'm glad you like them.

246
00:14:29,975 --> 00:14:31,933
Yes, they're not bad.

247
00:14:32,352 --> 00:14:35,144
The view from the top
of this tower is great, too.

248
00:14:35,688 --> 00:14:38,438
Now that we have
proper buildings and facilities,

249
00:14:38,525 --> 00:14:42,150
it might be time to start
officially calling this a town.

250
00:14:42,529 --> 00:14:44,112
First, it was Van Village,

251
00:14:44,197 --> 00:14:48,197
and now, I bet you're planning to call it
something silly like Van Town, aren't you?

252
00:14:48,493 --> 00:14:52,993
What's wrong with that?
I think Van Town would be a lovely name.

253
00:14:54,249 --> 00:14:55,916
It would be fitting.

254
00:14:56,001 --> 00:14:57,959
Van Town does have a nice ring to it.

255
00:14:58,253 --> 00:15:02,586
Seriously, I'm ending this conversation
before you actually start calling it that.

256
00:15:03,800 --> 00:15:05,925
Everyone just says whatever they want.

257
00:15:06,010 --> 00:15:07,468
Right, Lady Arte?

258
00:15:07,554 --> 00:15:09,054
Uh, yes.

259
00:15:09,764 --> 00:15:12,472
U-Um, Lord Van?

260
00:15:12,559 --> 00:15:13,600
What is it?

261
00:15:14,269 --> 00:15:20,519
I-If you don't mind, could you
just call me Arte from now on?

262
00:15:22,068 --> 00:15:23,318
Huh? Are you sure?

263
00:15:23,403 --> 00:15:28,070
Y-Yes. I think that will make it easier
for you to speak to me.

264
00:15:28,908 --> 00:15:30,658
Okay. "Arte" it is.

265
00:15:33,037 --> 00:15:36,245
Even though she asked me to say that,
she looks embarrassed.

266
00:15:41,713 --> 00:15:42,879
Okay, everyone.

267
00:15:43,089 --> 00:15:45,505
Would we all like some post-meal dessert?

268
00:15:45,591 --> 00:15:46,716
Dessert?

269
00:15:47,593 --> 00:15:49,134
Ta-da!

270
00:15:49,971 --> 00:15:51,096
Whoa!

271
00:15:51,180 --> 00:15:52,472
Cake!

272
00:15:52,556 --> 00:15:54,973
- Did you make this, Till?
- Yes.

273
00:15:55,059 --> 00:15:57,017
But how?

274
00:15:57,436 --> 00:16:00,436
After Bell and Rango
set up shop in the village,

275
00:16:00,522 --> 00:16:03,814
I was able to get all the ingredients
I needed to make a cake.

276
00:16:03,900 --> 00:16:05,734
Wow, really?

277
00:16:06,570 --> 00:16:07,737
Man.

278
00:16:08,239 --> 00:16:11,072
This might be turning
into a pretty nice village.

279
00:16:12,659 --> 00:16:14,534
It's delicious.

280
00:16:14,870 --> 00:16:15,911
Indeed.

281
00:16:15,996 --> 00:16:17,537
So delish.

282
00:16:18,123 --> 00:16:19,414
It's sweet.

283
00:16:19,833 --> 00:16:22,250
Huh? You're not having any, Till?

284
00:16:22,336 --> 00:16:26,794
I got a bit too into baking cakes lately,
so I've been eating cake every day.

285
00:16:27,508 --> 00:16:29,799
And my weight is in a perilous situation.

286
00:16:29,885 --> 00:16:31,926
I-I see.

287
00:16:32,262 --> 00:16:33,303
Hmm?

288
00:16:33,597 --> 00:16:35,430
What's the matter, Khamsin?

289
00:16:35,516 --> 00:16:37,307
Lord Van, look over there.

290
00:16:37,851 --> 00:16:40,268
They don't look like
soldiers or adventurers.

291
00:16:42,188 --> 00:16:43,313
I wonder who they are.

292
00:16:48,779 --> 00:16:52,737
U-Um, is this village Seatoh?

293
00:16:52,824 --> 00:16:54,574
Seatoh?

294
00:16:54,660 --> 00:16:59,076
I hear a people called the Seatoh lived on
this land before there was a village here.

295
00:16:59,330 --> 00:17:03,080
As a result, many refer
to this village as Seatoh.

296
00:17:03,418 --> 00:17:05,418
So this village did have a name all along?

297
00:17:05,503 --> 00:17:07,586
Then, it's really true.

298
00:17:08,048 --> 00:17:13,506
It's changed so drastically,
I still find it hard to believe.

299
00:17:13,594 --> 00:17:15,886
So what brings you here?

300
00:17:15,972 --> 00:17:18,597
We've come from the neighboring village.

301
00:17:18,683 --> 00:17:22,141
We are taxed heavily but we have
few young people to do the work.

302
00:17:22,228 --> 00:17:24,270
We can hardly make ends meet.

303
00:17:24,355 --> 00:17:27,772
So we came here to talk it over
with the folk in Seatoh.

304
00:17:27,858 --> 00:17:29,942
Why do you have few young people?

305
00:17:30,361 --> 00:17:33,320
Our young ones didn't choose
to leave the village.

306
00:17:33,573 --> 00:17:38,781
They were taken by the count to bolster
his forces in preparation for war.

307
00:17:38,869 --> 00:17:42,828
Oh, so they're from a village
in Ferdinatto County?

308
00:17:44,249 --> 00:17:47,874
I really shouldn't be welcoming
in people from another domain,

309
00:17:47,962 --> 00:17:51,503
but I'm fairly sure these people
risked their lives to make it this far.

310
00:17:54,343 --> 00:17:57,051
Then, what would you say
to relocating here?

311
00:17:57,137 --> 00:18:00,554
Y-You mean you'd take us in?

312
00:18:00,641 --> 00:18:03,183
But none of us have any money.

313
00:18:03,268 --> 00:18:06,310
That won't be an issue if you don't
have to pay taxes for a while.

314
00:18:06,396 --> 00:18:09,105
We have food, and I can
prepare homes for you.

315
00:18:09,608 --> 00:18:13,233
I-Is this heaven?

316
00:18:13,570 --> 00:18:16,237
How many villagers are there in total?

317
00:18:16,698 --> 00:18:21,406
Only ten of us made the trip today,
but our village's population is about 300.

318
00:18:21,495 --> 00:18:24,286
Will you be all right
with one house per family?

319
00:18:25,040 --> 00:18:28,540
I can't believe it.
This sounds like a dream.

320
00:18:29,044 --> 00:18:35,294
Okay, I'll get a few adventurers to go
with you to escort all the villagers here.

321
00:18:35,384 --> 00:18:39,134
Is it really all right for us
to accept such kindness?

322
00:18:39,221 --> 00:18:42,846
I'll also lend you some carriages
to help with your belongings.

323
00:18:42,932 --> 00:18:47,349
Oh, that won't be necessary.
We have cows, so they can carry all that.

324
00:18:47,437 --> 00:18:50,771
Cows? You have cows? Dairy cows?

325
00:18:51,024 --> 00:18:55,732
The county has rich pastures,
so we have ten cows.

326
00:18:55,820 --> 00:18:58,445
Wow. Cows, cows, cows!

327
00:18:58,532 --> 00:19:01,198
They produce milk. We can make
cheese, butter, and so on.

328
00:19:01,284 --> 00:19:03,950
This could be the village's
major new industry.

329
00:19:04,245 --> 00:19:05,828
That's right!

330
00:19:08,833 --> 00:19:11,958
Still, Lord Van sure is generous.

331
00:19:12,086 --> 00:19:15,253
He's taking in 300 people, just like that.

332
00:19:15,674 --> 00:19:18,632
Plus, the reward for this quest
is way too generous.

333
00:19:18,718 --> 00:19:20,385
Hey, you two.

334
00:19:20,469 --> 00:19:24,219
We're almost there, so keep a sharp eye
on our surroundings, will you?

335
00:19:24,307 --> 00:19:26,973
Last time, you two were
so absorbed in idle chitchat,

336
00:19:27,060 --> 00:19:29,768
we were attacked by
that forest dragon. Remember?

337
00:19:30,104 --> 00:19:31,271
Yeah, but that...

338
00:19:31,355 --> 00:19:32,605
That wasn't our fault.

339
00:19:32,690 --> 00:19:33,898
No talking back!

340
00:19:33,983 --> 00:19:36,483
Go on now! Back to your posts!

341
00:19:37,236 --> 00:19:38,695
Yes, ma'am.

342
00:19:42,658 --> 00:19:43,866
Are you okay?

343
00:19:45,869 --> 00:19:47,161
Yes, thank you.

344
00:19:47,663 --> 00:19:49,663
We're almost there. Hang in there.

345
00:19:50,249 --> 00:19:53,166
Honestly, I was against this.

346
00:19:54,962 --> 00:19:59,420
We're going from the middle of nowhere
to somewhere even more remote.

347
00:20:00,884 --> 00:20:01,968
It's true.

348
00:20:02,886 --> 00:20:05,136
You are heading to a more remote village.

349
00:20:05,931 --> 00:20:09,056
But this particular
remote village is paradise.

350
00:20:18,235 --> 00:20:20,443
Welcome to Seatoh.

351
00:20:26,577 --> 00:20:29,494
I'm sure you're all worn out
from your journey,

352
00:20:29,579 --> 00:20:31,746
so fill up on barbecued meat,

353
00:20:31,832 --> 00:20:35,082
then get a good night's rest
in the homes I've prepared for you.

354
00:20:37,963 --> 00:20:41,130
U-Um, i-is it really okay to eat it?

355
00:20:41,216 --> 00:20:43,258
Yup. Go eat your fill.

356
00:20:43,593 --> 00:20:44,760
Till?

357
00:20:44,970 --> 00:20:46,470
Leave it to me.

358
00:20:46,972 --> 00:20:49,139
Come on. Over here.

359
00:20:51,559 --> 00:20:53,101
Everyone, help yourselves.

360
00:20:53,811 --> 00:20:55,936
There's so much meat.

361
00:20:56,064 --> 00:20:57,731
Is it really okay to eat this?

362
00:20:57,815 --> 00:20:59,899
- It's delicious.
- Yum!

363
00:21:03,196 --> 00:21:04,613
It's so good.

364
00:21:11,329 --> 00:21:15,371
It was hard work preparing homes
and a barbecue for 300 people,

365
00:21:15,458 --> 00:21:17,125
but it was well worth the effort.

366
00:21:19,045 --> 00:21:20,878
Um, my lord?

367
00:21:21,213 --> 00:21:24,963
Is there, um, any work for us to do?

368
00:21:25,092 --> 00:21:26,259
Work?

369
00:21:26,761 --> 00:21:29,261
We want a way to earn a living.

370
00:21:29,346 --> 00:21:31,388
None of us have any savings.

371
00:21:31,641 --> 00:21:34,974
Oh, right. Everyone's
wracked with anxiety.

372
00:21:35,477 --> 00:21:36,644
Well...

373
00:21:37,104 --> 00:21:41,854
In that case, could I ask you to help run
the inn or the new shops we're opening?

374
00:21:41,943 --> 00:21:45,318
I'll also need people to help
cultivate some new fields.

375
00:21:45,404 --> 00:21:49,196
We can handle the fields,
but we've never run businesses before.

376
00:21:49,701 --> 00:21:51,034
It'll be fine.

377
00:21:51,410 --> 00:21:54,493
You can leave calculating the money
to those who can do it,

378
00:21:54,580 --> 00:21:57,288
so all you have to focus on
is what you're capable of.

379
00:21:58,542 --> 00:22:00,542
Ever since Lord Van came,

380
00:22:00,627 --> 00:22:04,544
life in this village has improved so much,
you'd hardly recognize it.

381
00:22:04,798 --> 00:22:10,423
So we'll all do everything we can to
help you enjoy your lives here as well.

382
00:22:12,931 --> 00:22:17,556
Is this really all right, though?
You're doing so much for us.

383
00:22:18,187 --> 00:22:20,520
Till, I think it's about time.

384
00:22:20,606 --> 00:22:21,731
Sure.

385
00:22:22,149 --> 00:22:23,733
Here you go.

386
00:22:25,861 --> 00:22:27,069
- What are those?
- Whoa.

387
00:22:27,738 --> 00:22:29,446
They're shortcakes.

388
00:22:29,740 --> 00:22:35,365
I asked your village chief to lend us some
of your cows' milk to make fresh cream.

389
00:22:36,329 --> 00:22:37,912
What is this?

390
00:22:37,998 --> 00:22:38,956
They look delicious.

391
00:22:39,082 --> 00:22:40,290
Thank you so much!

392
00:22:40,375 --> 00:22:45,208
You're doing us a favor by moving here,
so we're just helping each other.

393
00:22:48,717 --> 00:22:51,384
Soon enough, we'll have
a trading company in this village.

394
00:22:51,469 --> 00:22:55,052
This village will develop even further
and get even more comfortable,

395
00:22:55,140 --> 00:22:58,223
so I hope you'll all relax
and enjoy your new lives here.

396
00:23:02,939 --> 00:23:06,356
I think I might actually be able
to live a good life here.

397
00:23:06,442 --> 00:23:07,692
Me, too.

398
00:23:08,028 --> 00:23:09,694
- Same here.
- Me, too! Me, too!

399
00:23:09,905 --> 00:23:13,113
Everyone had their hands full
just trying to survive,

400
00:23:13,199 --> 00:23:17,574
but they have hope now, and their minds
have turned to how to enjoy their lives.

401
00:23:19,080 --> 00:23:20,164
Lord Van.

402
00:23:21,249 --> 00:23:23,249
The village's population has grown,

403
00:23:23,334 --> 00:23:26,084
but we're still a long way
from being a city of 10,000.

404
00:23:26,171 --> 00:23:29,504
You'll need to continue
developing this village.

405
00:23:33,469 --> 00:23:34,761
All right.

406
00:23:34,845 --> 00:23:38,012
I'll keep working hard
on my task of city building!

407
00:23:39,975 --> 00:23:44,809
NEXT EPISODE: A POSTAPOCALYPTIC BAND'S
ROWDY DUNGEON EXPLORATION
